Motherhood requires sacrifices. While some moms choose to hire a nanny to help with taking care of their children, others feel more comfortable sending their children to crèche from a young age. There are also some mothers who would much rather be care for their kids full time by quitting their day jobs for a year or two. But what is it like transitioning from being a working mom to one who stays at home with the kids? Chanté (29) is a former nurse and mother to a one-year-old and a two-month-old. After six years of nursing, Chanté decided to quit her job and take care of her children full time. 